{
  "query": "What is the most effective design for an artificial nest box intended for bumblebees?",
  "relevant_summary": "Replicated trials report that the most effective design is a nest box entirely buried 5\u201310 cm underground with a 30\u201380 cm long entrance pipe; seven trials in the USA, Canada, or UK found 6\u201358% occupancy for underground boxes [48]. Wooden surface or above\u2011ground boxes commonly marketed for wildlife gardening are not the most effective; four trials that directly compared designs found underground, false\u2011underground, or aerial boxes were more readily occupied than wooden surface boxes [48]. Several types have been used successfully, including wooden or brick/tile boxes at the ground surface, underground tin/wood/terracotta boxes, and boxes attached to trees [48]. Three UK trials since 1989 of various non\u2011underground designs had very low uptake (0\u20132.5%) [48], and two additional replicated trials of bumblebee nest boxes reported very low uptake (\u22642%) [80].",
  "action_ids": [
